  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Kitchen Assistant",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a motivated and disciplined Kitchen Assistant to train directly under our renowned Head Chef, Yuji Sato. This role is designed for individuals who are serious about building a long-term career in Japanese cuisine and fine dining. The successful candidate will receive hands-on mentorship in a high-performance omakase kitchen, with exposure to classical Japanese techniques, premium ingredients, and exacting service standards.</p><h2>Training & Development</h2><ul><li><p>Direct mentorship under Chef Yuji Sato</p></li><li><p>Progressive training in:</p><ul><li><p>Japanese knife skills</p></li><li><p>Ingredient handling (fish, seafood, wagyu, rice, dashi)</p></li><li><p>Kitchen discipline and fine-dining standards</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Opportunity for advancement to Commis Chef based on performance</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><h3>Essential</h3><ul><li><p>Strong interest in Japanese cuisine and fine dining</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn, take instructions, and accept feedback</p></li><li><p>High level of discipline, punctuality, and work ethic</p></li><li><p>Able to work long hours, weekends, and public holidays</p></li><li><p>Physically fit and able to stand for long periods</p></li><li><p>Basic understanding of kitchen hygiene and safety</p></li></ul><h3>Preferred</h3><ul><li><p>Culinary school training or prior kitchen experience</p></li><li><p>Basic knife skills</p></li><li><p>Experience in Japanese or fine-dining kitchens</p></li><li><p>Long-term career aspiration in professional cooking</p></li></ul><h2>Personal Qualities</h2><ul><li><p>Humble, patient, and eager to learn</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented and precise</p></li><li><p>Calm under pressure</p></li><li><p>Respectful of hierarchy and kitchen discipline</p></li><li><p>Passionate about craftsmanship and continuous improvement</p></li></ul><h2>What We Offer</h2><ul><li><p>Rare opportunity to train under a respected Japanese chef</p></li><li><p>Structured on-the-job training in a premium omakase environment</p></li></ul>",
